pkgc:ID_553775121 a skos:Concept ;
    dc:date "2025-01-28"^^xsd:date ;
    skos:prefLabel """Your New Gig at dvlr Logistics: The Short & Snarky Version

Cash Money: You're getting N300,000 every month. Pay your own taxes, especially to Lagos State, because we're not your accountant.
Clock In, Clock Out: Work is from 9am to 5pm, Monday to Friday. Sometimes, you'll work late because the job's a diva. Lunch break? Anytime between 1pm and 3pm, but keep it to an hour.
Contract Duration: We're starting with a 3-month contract that renews monthly. We'll check if you're doing great at 3 months and again at 12. If you're killing it, we keep you; if not, bye-bye.
Performance Review: After 6 months of proving yourself, we'll review your performance. Bring two good references: one from your old boss, two from friends (not family). Either of us can say "it's not you, it's me" with a month's notice or pay in lieu.
Firing Squad: If you mess up big time or trash our rep, we can fire you on the spot. No notice, no pay. Harsh, but fair.
Vacation Time: After 6 months, you get 15 days off per year, added monthly. Check the handbook for all the leave details.
Code of Conduct: Follow our rules, or else. It's all in the handbook.
Sick Days: If you're too sick or hurt to work for more than a week, get a doctor's note. Update weekly or we'll think you're faking it and fire you.
Shh, It's Secret: We'll share juicy company secrets with you. Keep them secret or face the wrath. When you leave, return all company stuff and delete any copies. No blabbing, ever, unless we say so. If someone asks, tell us within 24 hours.
Non-Disclosure: There's a separate NDA. Read it, sign it, live by it.

Sign and send this back in 3 days if you're in. Got questions? Hit up HR. Welcome to dvlr logistics, where we hope you succeed, or at least don't screw up too badly!""" ;
    pkg:sourceMap "ajared.mm" .

