pkgc:ID_559831432 a skos:Concept ;
    dc:date "2025-01-28"^^xsd:date ;
    skos:prefLabel "**Welcome to Your New Job! Here’s the Fun (and Serious) Stuff You Need to Know:**" ;
    pkg:sourceMap "ajared.mm" .

pkgc:ID_560391896 a skos:Concept ;
    dc:date "2025-01-28"^^xsd:date ;
    skos:prefLabel """The terms of employment shall be as follows: \r
1.	REMUNERATION\r
This offer attracts a guaranteed gross remuneration of N300, 000 (Amount in Words) per month. Please note your responsibility for handling any income tax requirements,  particularly Tax to the Lagos State Government.                                                  \r
2.	WORKING HOURS\r
The Company’s official working hours are between the hours of 9:00am and 5.00pm, Monday to Friday. However, you may be expected from time to time, to work beyond the regular working hours and as the job demands. You shall also be entitled to a 1-hour lunch break each day between 1:00pm and 3:00pm.\r
3.	CONTRACT DURATION: This contract is a monthly renewable contract for 3 months. Your performance would be reviewed at the end of the first initial  months and at the end of the 12-month period, and your contract renewed based on the company’s performance and need for the position and also on you meeting set targets.  \r
\r
4.	PERFORMANCE REVIEW\r
A performance review will follow after a six (6) month period of probation, we would also require the receipt of two (2) favorable references, one of who should be your previous employer and the other two, character references who are not related to you. During the contract period, either party may terminate this contract by giving 1 months’ notice or payment of equivalent salary in lieu of such notice. There may be review of contract fees at the point of renewal of contract.  \r
5.	TERMINATION OF APPOINTMENT\r
Either you or the Company may terminate the employment by giving, to the other, one (1) months’ notice, or paying one (1) months’ basic salary in lieu of the requisite notice, after confirmation of Employment. \r
In the case of a severe breach of corporate policies and guidelines or misconduct, which may damage the good name and reputation of the Company, the Company shall reserve the right to immediately terminate the services of the employee in question, without giving one (1) months’ notice or payment in lieu of notice. \r
\r
6.	ANNUAL VACATION\r
You will be entitled to an annual vacation of 15 (Fifteen) working days after your initial 6 months period with the company. This is accruable on a monthly basis from commencement of work. The employee handbook stipulates company policy on annual, casual and maternity/paternity leave.\r
\r
7.	CODE OF CONDUCT\r
You are expected to observe and comply with the Company’s code of conduct; rules; regulations and ethical standards as contained in the employee handbook and other company policies upon resumption\r
\r
8.	INCAPACITY\r
If you are incapacitated and unable to perform your duties due to illness, or an accident, or injury, you shall report this promptly to the Company. If you are so prevented from performing your duties for more than 7 days, you are required to present a medical practitioner’s certificate stating the condition leading to the absence. Such medical certificates shall be renewed on a weekly basis so that the whole period of your absence is certified by such medical certificates. Where you fail to provide the requisite certificate within the specified period, the Company shall treat such absence as a breach of the employment terms by you entitling the Company to terminate this contract of employment immediately and without further notice.\r
\r
9.	CONFIDENTIATLITY\r
The Parties intend to engage in substantive discussions and sharing of confidential information to enable you perform your contractual obligations. In connection with these discussions, it may be necessary and/or desirable for the Company to provide you with, or allow access to, proprietary, technical, or business data, and/or other confidential information of the Company. \r
\r
The Company believes, and you hereby agree, that it’s Confidential Information has significant commercial value that would be diminished by unauthorized disclosure; therefore, you agree that you are under an obligation of confidentiality. Accordingly, the commitments of confidentiality in this Agreement are a condition to the Company’s willingness to hire/engage you as its employee.\r
\r
The above in view, you will not, either during the continuance of your employment or thereafter, use to the detriment or prejudice of the Company except in the proper course of duties, divulge to any person any trade secret or other confidential information concerning the business or affairs of the company which have come to your knowledge during your employment. In the event of cessation of your employment for whatever reason you will return to the company all documents relating to the company’s affairs which might be in your possession and destroy all copies of same that may be in your possession (hard and soft). \r
\r
You agree that during your employment with the Company and following the termination of such employment for any reason, you shall not directly or indirectly divulge or make use of any Confidential Information outside of your employment with the Company, without the prior written consent of the Company. You also agree that if you are questioned about such Confidential Information by anyone not authorized to receive such information, including government authorities, regulators, and the courts, you will notify the Company within 24 hours of such questioning.\r
\r
Acceptance of this offer constitutes an undertaking that you will not remove or make copies of any Confidential Information and documentation/papers for non-company related use during the course of your employment with dlvr or after termination of same without prior written notice from authorized personnel. You acknowledge that applicable law may impose longer duties of nondisclosure and that such longer periods are not shortened by this agreement. You will also during the continuance of your employment comply with the terms of the company data protection policy.\r
\r
10.	NON-DISCLOSURE\r
A non-disclosure agreement has been attached to this offer. You are expected to abide by terms as stated in the agreement.\r
\r
We shall be grateful if you will sign and return the enclosed copy of this letter signifying your acceptance of our offer within three working days. If you have any queries or would like to discuss the contents of this letter, please do not hesitate to contact Human Resources.\r
\r
We look forward to welcoming you as an employee of dvlr logistics Limited and we wish you success in your new position here at the dvlr logistics.\r""" ;
    pkg:sourceMap "ajared.mm" .

